- Get out now!

261
00:21:05,033 --> 00:21:06,943
Please don't go too far.

262
00:21:06,943 --> 00:21:09,543
We are also going crazy because it's unfair to us!

263
00:21:09,543 --> 00:21:12,353
We are also in a living h*ll!

264
00:21:12,353 --> 00:21:15,573
I get what you mean. But please, let's go outside!

265
00:21:15,573 --> 00:21:18,444
Let's talk outside. Shall we?

266
00:21:18,444 --> 00:21:20,523
Seong Min, listen to me.

267
00:21:20,523 --> 00:21:23,783
Geun Ho might hurt himself sometimes.

268
00:21:23,783 --> 00:21:25,933
But he's not someone who can hit other people.

269
00:21:25,933 --> 00:21:28,093
So how could he have done that to the grandmother?

270
00:21:28,093 --> 00:21:30,793
I know. I also know that very well, Hyung.

271
00:21:30,793 --> 00:21:34,063
This doesn't make any sense.

272
00:21:34,063 --> 00:21:37,443
But you can't act this way here!

273
00:21:37,443 --> 00:21:40,113
Why? Why?

274
00:21:40,113 --> 00:21:42,693
My son is in jail for nothing!

275
00:21:42,693 --> 00:21:44,943
Do you think he'll be okay in there?

276
00:21:44,943 --> 00:21:48,183
What if something happens to him?

277
00:21:48,183 --> 00:21:51,033
All right. I get it so let's talk outside. Okay?

278
00:21:51,033 --> 00:21:54,933
- Seong Min.
- Hyung, I get it! Let's take it outside.

279
00:21:54,933 --> 00:21:56,503
- Let's talk outside.
- Please!

280
00:21:56,503 --> 00:21:58,193
Put on your shoes.

281
00:21:58,193 --> 00:22:00,583
How can they act that way?

282
00:22:04,493 --> 00:22:06,253
- You're back, Professor.
- Yes. Did you eat lunch?

283
00:22:06,253 --> 00:22:08,953
Yes. But Professor, look.

284
00:22:11,303 --> 00:22:13,513
I feel Sunbae Dae Beom is acting weird.

285
00:22:13,513 --> 00:22:15,303
Why? What about him?

286
00:22:15,303 --> 00:22:18,863
He murmured in front of the chalkboard the whole day,

287
00:22:18,863 --> 00:22:21,073
and he ran to the library out of the blue.

288
00:22:21,073 --> 00:22:22,843
Is that so?

289
00:22:24,133 --> 00:22:28,153
Welcome, Ahn Dae Beom.

290
00:22:28,153 --> 00:22:29,583
Pardon?

291
00:22:29,583 --> 00:22:33,263
He went into the black hole like old times.

292
00:22:33,263 --> 00:22:38,013
We'll see what he brings out from there.

293
00:22:38,623 --> 00:22:40,073
Where's Seong Chul?

294
00:22:40,073 --> 00:22:41,453
He went out for a break.

295
00:22:41,453 --> 00:22:42,983
He needs a break.

296
00:22:42,983 --> 00:22:45,633
He should take as much rest as he needs. And Eun Mi,

297
00:22:45,633 --> 00:22:49,873
last year's conference data on Seong Chul's laptop, find it and send it to me.

298
00:22:49,873 --> 00:22:51,843
I'll send it on messenger app, Professor.

299
00:22:51,843 --> 00:22:53,933
Okay.

300
00:22:55,060 --> 00:22:57,460
[File sent]

301
00:22:57,943 --> 00:23:00,213
I just sent it.

302
00:23:07,177 --> 00:23:09,863
[Professor, I posted it on the anonymous board.]

303
00:23:09,863 --> 00:23:11,823
[Good job.]

304
00:23:16,893 --> 00:23:20,613
[Angok Funeral Home]

305
00:23:54,473 --> 00:23:56,573
I'm sorry.

306
00:24:02,551 --> 00:24:04,591
Grandma...

307
00:24:09,293 --> 00:24:11,503
I'm so sorry.

308
00:24:34,113 --> 00:24:36,043
Grandma.

309
00:24:37,386 --> 00:24:44,386
When you go to Heaven, please go see my mom.

310
00:24:46,983 --> 00:24:52,413
I think my mom will like you a lot.

311
00:24:55,923 --> 00:25:01,773
I asked my mom if she was sad when my dad passed away,

312
00:25:01,773 --> 00:25:04,813
and she told me this:

313
00:25:08,175 --> 00:25:12,895
"Life is like a bus trip."

314
00:25:14,431 --> 00:25:17,391
"I'm the driver of the bus,"

315
00:25:18,149 --> 00:25:22,553
"and my parents, friends,"

316
00:25:22,553 --> 00:25:26,333
"and those I briefly met are all on the bus,"

317
00:25:27,239 --> 00:25:31,869
"but they will all get off someday."

318
00:25:38,872 --> 00:25:43,059
We hope she goes to a comfortable, nice place

319
00:25:43,059 --> 00:25:45,028
and rests in peace now.

320
00:25:45,028 --> 00:25:49,358
Now she's going on her final long trip.

321
00:25:49,358 --> 00:25:55,012
Let's all do a slight bow to pray that her journey will be comfortable.

322
00:25:55,012 --> 00:25:57,002
Bow, please.

323
00:25:58,603 --> 00:26:02,763
I don't know if my mom truly believed those words or not,

324
00:26:04,693 --> 00:26:08,503
but I think she had to believe in them to endure.

325
00:26:09,943 --> 00:26:13,793
She had to believe a farewell is not a big deal.

326
00:26:13,793 --> 00:26:15,683
Stand straight, please.

327
00:26:17,633 --> 00:26:19,793
We'll close the door now.

328
00:26:20,423 --> 00:26:22,493
Grandma.

329
00:26:22,493 --> 00:26:27,513
Whenever I saw you, you reminded me of my mom.

330
00:26:31,443 --> 00:26:34,343
All you have done for me,

331
00:26:34,343 --> 00:26:36,933
I won't forget.

332
00:26:45,243 --> 00:26:47,433
Grandma.

333
00:26:47,433 --> 00:26:49,743
Goodbye.

334
00:26:51,103 --> 00:26:53,063
Farewell.

335
00:27:06,710 --> 00:27:08,843
Agasshi, you're back!

336
00:27:08,843 --> 00:27:12,263
I kept waiting for you to come home.

337
00:27:12,263 --> 00:27:15,383
- Can you come to my place and talk for a second?
- No.

338
00:27:15,383 --> 00:27:17,933
I... I have something for you.

339
00:27:17,933 --> 00:27:19,563
Can you come with me for a second, please?

340
00:27:19,563 --> 00:27:22,073
- No, I have nothing to say to you.
- No, please. I'm sorry.

341
00:27:22,073 --> 00:27:24,753
- What are you doing right now?
- Young Lady, please!

342
00:27:24,753 --> 00:27:27,123
It won't take a lot of time.

343
00:27:27,123 --> 00:27:30,033
I'll make it quick and brief!

344
00:27:30,033 --> 00:27:33,243
Here, come inside.

345
00:27:33,243 --> 00:27:35,863
Come, come.

346
00:27:35,863 --> 00:27:38,283
Have a seat. Do you want something to drink?

347
00:27:38,283 --> 00:27:41,275
No, should I put together a meal? Aren't you hungry?

348
00:27:41,275 --> 00:27:43,775
No, I don't want to eat.

349
00:27:44,763 --> 00:27:48,423
Look at this. This is a petition for my son.

350
00:27:48,423 --> 00:27:51,663
Can't you sign this for me?

351
00:27:52,313 --> 00:27:53,763
No, I won't sign it.

352
00:27:53,763 --> 00:27:57,323
No, please! Young Lady.

353
00:27:57,323 --> 00:28:01,893
I understand it won't be easy for you to sign this from your perspective. But, please.

354
00:28:01,893 --> 00:28:05,893
Please do something for my son. Please, I beg you.

355
00:28:05,893 --> 00:28:10,623
If I think about my poor baby shivering in jail...

356
00:28:10,623 --> 00:28:12,713
Ajumeoni.

357
00:28:12,713 --> 00:28:15,623
The one who wrote graffiti in the past was my Geun Ho.

358
00:28:15,623 --> 00:28:18,623
But this incident really has nothing to do with my son.

359
00:28:18,623 --> 00:28:20,323
Why do you keep acting like this?

360
00:28:20,323 --> 00:28:24,703
Listen! My son lost his glasses the day before the incident so he wasn't wearing them that day.

361
00:28:24,703 --> 00:28:27,163
But if he doesn't wear them, he can't see anything!

362
00:28:27,163 --> 00:28:29,143
How could he have written the graffiti that day?

363
00:28:29,143 --> 00:28:30,583
Please stop this.

364
00:28:30,583 --> 00:28:32,683
Agasshi, please!

365
00:28:32,683 --> 00:28:34,683
Please, I beg you.

366
00:28:34,683 --> 00:28:38,023
Can you please sign this for me? Please, please.

367
00:28:38,023 --> 00:28:40,893
Seriously, how can you act this way?

368
00:28:40,893 --> 00:28:43,893
How can you be this selfish?

369
00:28:44,650 --> 00:28:47,903
Bom's grandmother passed away due to Geun Ho.

370
00:28:47,903 --> 00:28:49,953
That's not true!

371
00:28:49,953 --> 00:28:53,883
When you came to the billiards and said don't report Geun Ho for the graffiti,

372
00:28:53,883 --> 00:28:58,453
Grandma said Geun Ho is a sweet boy.

373
00:28:58,453 --> 00:29:02,803
She said Geun Ho's a sweet boy and I shouldn't report him.

374
00:29:02,803 --> 00:29:06,160
But he killed Grandma!

375
00:29:06,160 --> 00:29:08,150
Aren't you sorry for her?

376
00:29:08,153 --> 00:29:11,193
How can you only worry about your child?

377
00:29:11,193 --> 00:29:13,813
My Geun Ho didn't do it!

378
00:29:20,870 --> 00:29:23,013
Oh? Unnie.

379
00:29:23,013 --> 00:29:25,770
- Are you coming from the lab?
- Yes.

380
00:29:25,770 --> 00:29:27,833
You look tired.

381
00:29:27,833 --> 00:29:33,113
Sunbae Dae Beom is solving the problem without eating or sleeping.

382
00:29:33,113 --> 00:29:36,463
Compared to him, I'm not tired at all.

383
00:29:36,463 --> 00:29:38,253
Is that so?

384
00:29:40,590 --> 00:29:44,987
But I don't know why I feel sorry for him.

385
00:29:45,890 --> 00:29:47,903
Why do you feel sorry for him?

386
00:29:47,903 --> 00:29:54,380
I called you to bring him no matter what

387
00:29:55,050 --> 00:29:58,403
because the ethics committee was investigating.

388
00:29:58,403 --> 00:30:01,503
But that's not your fault.

389
00:30:02,920 --> 00:30:06,543
I know, right. I'll see you later.

390
00:30:07,390 --> 00:30:08,993
See you.

391
00:30:11,420 --> 00:30:13,083
Unnie.

392
00:30:57,280 --> 00:30:59,443
Bom.

393
00:31:00,740 --> 00:31:04,813
Ha Neul. Let's have a talk for a second.

394
00:31:08,120 --> 00:31:11,170
Bom, I'm sorry.

395
00:31:11,170 --> 00:31:13,673
I'm sorry.

396
00:31:13,673 --> 00:31:16,963
Ha Neul, I'm sorry.

397
00:31:16,963 --> 00:31:21,000
I'm so sorry I showed only my bad side as your dad.

398
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:23,090
I'm so sorry.

399
00:31:23,093 --> 00:31:26,910
I won't drink ever again.

400
00:31:26,910 --> 00:31:29,190
And I'll only live for you guys.

401
00:31:29,193 --> 00:31:32,243
I'll try hard. So please forgive me just once.

402
00:31:32,243 --> 00:31:34,470
Please give me one chance.

403
00:31:34,470 --> 00:31:36,260
I'm sorry.

404
00:31:36,263 --> 00:31:39,963
Dad, stand up. Please stand up now.

405
00:31:43,470 --> 00:31:46,043
Now it's just we three.

406
00:31:47,180 --> 00:31:49,133
Since my mom passed away...

407
00:31:51,070 --> 00:31:53,316
I only have you guys.

408
00:31:58,320 --> 00:31:59,883
Here.

409
00:32:03,670 --> 00:32:07,743
This is the money left over from the funeral.

410
00:32:07,743 --> 00:32:10,053
Let's use this for our living expenses.

411
00:32:12,150 --> 00:32:14,743
I'm starting a new job tomorrow.

412
00:32:14,743 --> 00:32:19,523
Now on, I'll probably come home late from work.

413
00:32:21,210 --> 00:32:23,753
I'll try my best.

414
00:32:23,753 --> 00:32:26,120
Take it. Why don't you take care of this money, Bom?

415
00:32:26,120 --> 00:32:28,350
Give Ha Neul some pocket money.

416
00:32:30,980 --> 00:32:33,013
I'm so sorry.

417
00:32:35,410 --> 00:32:37,073
Just take it.

418
00:33:27,520 --> 00:33:31,260
[Korean writing practice paper]

419
00:33:38,373 --> 00:33:45,173
[Kim Jung Hoon, Kim Bom, Kim Ha Neul]

420
00:33:51,300 --> 00:33:54,723
I'm sorry, Grandma.

421
00:33:59,690 --> 00:34:02,730
Grandma, I'm sorry.

422
00:34:34,150 --> 00:34:36,823
When I first came here,

423
00:34:36,823 --> 00:34:41,373
I had nothing more to lose.

424
00:34:46,300 --> 00:34:50,503
I had no idea how to live from then on.

425
00:34:53,010 --> 00:34:55,813
My confidence was at its lowest.

426
00:34:58,490 --> 00:35:04,100
♫ Life feels overwhelming ♫

427
00:35:04,100 --> 00:35:09,580
♫ Loneliness all the while ♫

428
00:35:09,580 --> 00:35:15,110
♫ Who remains standing ♫

429
00:35:15,110 --> 00:35:19,843
Then... I met people here.

430
00:35:23,950 --> 00:35:25,823
Bom.

431
00:35:25,823 --> 00:35:27,693
Jae Hoon.

432
00:35:29,560 --> 00:35:31,473
Grandma.

433
00:35:32,410 --> 00:35:34,493
Dae Beom.

434
00:35:38,990 --> 00:35:43,390
♫ I want the days to move slower ♫

435
00:35:43,390 --> 00:35:47,913
They helped me smile again.

436
00:35:52,790 --> 00:35:57,753
I got rehabilitation every day in this town.

437
00:35:59,030 --> 00:36:05,530
♫ Hear this ordinary, friendly song ♫

438
00:36:07,900 --> 00:36:13,493
But I shouldn't have come to this town.

439
00:36:16,780 --> 00:36:19,933
If they hadn't met me,

440
00:36:22,000 --> 00:36:27,323
Dae Beom wouldn't recall his painful past,

441
00:36:29,300 --> 00:36:33,010
and Grandma would have

442
00:36:33,010 --> 00:36:36,160
a long, happy life with Bom and Ha Neul.

443
00:36:42,230 --> 00:36:47,933
I shouldn't have come to this place.

444
00:36:54,640 --> 00:36:58,843
Let's wrap it up at this level of what Dae Beom is working on, okay?

445
00:36:58,843 --> 00:37:01,053
- Okay.
- All right.

446
00:37:01,053 --> 00:37:03,553
Let's not go too deep into it.

447
00:37:03,553 --> 00:37:05,003
Hello.

448
00:37:05,003 --> 00:37:06,703
Welcome.

449
00:37:12,510 --> 00:37:14,703
- Professor Lee.
- Yes?

450
00:37:14,703 --> 00:37:17,413
Is it okay to leave Dae Beom alone like that?

451
00:37:17,413 --> 00:37:18,663
What about it?

452
00:37:18,663 --> 00:37:22,303
I mean, he's studying without even sleeping.

453
00:37:22,303 --> 00:37:24,183
That's the real Dae Beom.

454
00:37:24,183 --> 00:37:27,723
I guess you didn't know. He goes crazy if he doesn't know an answer.

455
00:37:27,723 --> 00:37:30,103
- Eun Mi.
- Yes?

456
00:37:31,440 --> 00:37:36,373
He completely went into his cave, like old times.

457
00:37:45,840 --> 00:37:51,213
Sunbae Seong Chul wrote that post on the anonymous board.

458
00:37:51,213 --> 00:37:53,543
Why would he do that?

459
00:37:55,710 --> 00:37:58,413
Professor Lee made him do it.

460
00:37:58,413 --> 00:38:02,273
And Prof Lee asked the Dean to set up the call to the Dutch professor.

461
00:38:02,273 --> 00:38:06,563
So he made Dae Beom meet him on purpose.

462
00:38:06,563 --> 00:38:08,683
Wait.

463
00:38:08,683 --> 00:38:11,443
What does that even mean?

464
00:38:12,390 --> 00:38:14,660
I think Prof Lee purposely did this

465
00:38:14,660 --> 00:38:19,100
to make Dae Beom write a paper with him.

466
00:38:25,383 --> 00:38:28,033
- Ji Young.
- Yes?

467
00:38:28,033 --> 00:38:31,193
I think you need to find a place to live with Dae Beom again.

468
00:38:36,753 --> 00:38:38,323
Noona!

469
00:38:40,203 --> 00:38:41,843
Gyeo Wool, Noona is here!

470
00:38:43,053 --> 00:38:44,913
Gyeo Wool!

471
00:38:44,913 --> 00:38:47,593
My Gyeo Wool.

472
00:38:47,593 --> 00:38:49,983
Have you been well?

473
00:38:52,923 --> 00:38:56,133
It was just a few days, but he's so excited to see you.

474
00:38:57,103 --> 00:38:59,313
Thank you for taking care of him.

475
00:38:59,313 --> 00:39:01,233
No problem.

476
00:39:02,993 --> 00:39:04,653
Gyeo Wool.

477
00:39:05,753 --> 00:39:07,383
Noona.

478
00:39:08,833 --> 00:39:11,263
I might leave this town soon.

479
00:39:11,263 --> 00:39:12,653
What?

480
00:39:14,413 --> 00:39:18,823
My parents asked me to return to America.

481
00:39:20,928 --> 00:39:24,098
Did you tell this to Bom?

482
00:39:25,603 --> 00:39:27,693
No.

483
00:39:27,693 --> 00:39:31,433
Bom is going through a lot right now; I couldn't talk of this.

484
00:39:38,493 --> 00:39:41,643
I'm still immature and childish.

485
00:39:43,503 --> 00:39:46,733
I don't think I'm suitable for her.

486
00:39:48,223 --> 00:39:52,933
Noona, I'm scared.

487
00:39:52,933 --> 00:39:54,990
I fear I'll drift apart from Bom.

488
00:39:55,783 --> 00:39:57,863
I fear I'll be forgotten.

489
00:40:05,443 --> 00:40:07,303
Jae Hoon.

490
00:40:10,983 --> 00:40:15,553
If anyone drifts from you, let them.

491
00:40:15,553 --> 00:40:20,193
If anybody hates you, let them.

492
00:40:20,193 --> 00:40:22,613
But for me,

493
00:40:22,613 --> 00:40:28,393
I'll always like you the same as now, when or wherever I see you again.

494
00:40:29,423 --> 00:40:31,933
When we see each other again,

495
00:40:31,933 --> 00:40:35,133
I'll run to you with a smile and a big hug.

496
00:40:35,983 --> 00:40:37,813
I'll say, "It's been a while."

497
00:40:37,813 --> 00:40:41,053
I'll ask how you've been and say, "I missed you."

498
00:40:43,263 --> 00:40:45,163
That's how much...

499
00:40:46,803 --> 00:40:50,053
you are a good person to me.

500
00:40:51,203 --> 00:40:52,933
Noona...

501
00:40:55,153 --> 00:40:57,483
And...

502
00:40:57,483 --> 00:41:00,193
I think Bom thinks of you the same way I do.

503
00:41:05,453 --> 00:41:07,243
Thank you.

504
00:41:22,153 --> 00:41:24,153
Hello?

505
00:41:24,153 --> 00:41:26,643
Seong Min,

506
00:41:26,643 --> 00:41:28,883
are you happy?

507
00:41:28,883 --> 00:41:30,432
What?

508
00:41:30,432 --> 00:41:32,326
What are you saying out of the blue?

509
00:41:32,326 --> 00:41:35,486
I came to Seoul, but why am I unhappy?

510
00:41:37,713 --> 00:41:40,570
Ji Young, did something happen to you?

511
00:41:41,817 --> 00:41:44,173
I miss Angok, where nothing happens.

512
00:41:44,173 --> 00:41:46,650
What "nothing happens"?

513
00:41:46,650 --> 00:41:49,250
The town became a mess.

514
00:41:49,873 --> 00:41:53,613
Is it due to Dae Beom again?

515
00:41:53,613 --> 00:41:57,043
I don't know what to do with Dae Beom.

516
00:41:57,043 --> 00:42:01,563
I guess Dae Beom has it tough since Yeo Reum is leaving here.

517
00:42:01,563 --> 00:42:03,263
What are you saying?

518
00:42:03,263 --> 00:42:05,133
Didn't you know?

519
00:42:05,133 --> 00:42:07,963
Yeo Reum is leaving this town soon.

520
00:42:08,993 --> 00:42:11,613
Hello? Ji Young?

521
00:42:11,613 --> 00:42:13,223
Hello?

522
00:42:38,513 --> 00:42:40,943
It's been a while.

523
00:42:44,073 --> 00:42:46,113
I missed you.

524
00:42:53,813 --> 00:42:56,073
You must be enduring a lot.

525
00:42:57,453 --> 00:42:59,643
Did you eat anything?

